#### Profane Sigils
*6th-level Mark of Wrath feature*

<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You can brand creatures with debilitating sigils. As a bonus action, choose one creature you can see within 30 feet of you. The target is branded for 1 minute with a sigil of your choice from the list below. 

The brand ends early if the target dies, you die, or you are incapacitated. Once you brand a target, you can’t do so again until you finish a short or long rest.

##### Sigil of Binding
A creature affected by this sigil cannot take the Dash or Disengage action. If the creature attempts to teleport or leave their current plane via ability, spell, or portal, they take chaos damage equal to your demon hunter level and must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failure, the teleport or plane shift fails.

##### Sigil of Chains

<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | CLASSES</div>

\pagebreakNum

##### Sigil of Flame

##### Sigil of Misery

##### Sigil of Silence

##### Sigil of Weakness
You gain a bonus to damage rolls against the cursed target. The bonus equals your proficiency bonus. Any attack roll you make against the cursed target is a critical hit on a roll of 19 or 20 on the d20.

#### Chaos Brand
*10th-level Mark of Wrath feature*

<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

Your Profane Sigils feature digs dark arcane scars into your target, leaving them vulnerable to your magic. A creature branded by you has disadvantage on saving throws against your warlock spells.

#### Unleashed Power
*15th-level Mark of Wrath feature*

<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

As a bonus action, you can regain an expended spell slot by invoking a number of fel points equal to the spell's level. You cannot use this feature to restore a spell slot with a higher slot level than you can cast through Fel Sorcery, and each time you use this feature after the first, you must spend an additional fel point.

#### Relentless Rage
*18th-level Mark of Wrath feature*

<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

When you use your action to cast a spell, you can make one weapon attack as a bonus action.

