## Fel Secrets

### Analyze Blood
**[Based on [this spell.](https://www.dndbeyond.com/spells/11498-analyze-blood) Potentially also the Blood Hunter's Grim Psychometry ability.]**

### Brand of the Hunt
**[Can mark a target with a brand that lets you know where they are and allows you to teleport short distances to them.]**

### Consume Magic
*Prerequisite: 9th level*

While you have an active Chaos Blades, when you hit a creature, object, or magical effect with that weapon, you can spend 2 fel points to cast *dispel magic* as a bonus action against the target. If you successfully dispel a spell, you gain a number of temporary hit points equal to your proficiency bonus plus the spell's level.

### Immolation Aura
You can spend 1 fel point to engulf yourself in flames for 1 minute, shedding bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light in an additional 30 feet. 

For the duration, a creature that ends its turn within 5 feet of you, touches you, or hits you with a melee attack while within 5 feet of you takes fire damage equal to half your demon hunter level.

### Immortal Soul
*Prerequisite: 15th level*

If you are killed, your soul is drawn into the Twisting Nether, where your body will eventually reform in a random location within 1d10 days. When it does, your original body decays rapidly to dust. You can still be returned to life through spells like *raise dead* before this occurs.

When you are returned to life this way, you have a −4 penalty to all attack rolls, saving throws, and ability checks. Every time you finish a long rest, the penalty is reduced by 1 until it disappears. If you are killed again while you have this penalty, you die permanently. 

**[Based on a lich phylactery. How would a character with this get back to the party?]**

### Infernal Strike
**[Based on an infernal's meteoric impact.]**

### Master of Chains
**[Benefits when wielding whip, spiked chain, similar weapons. Can cause the weapon to expand and bind/trip opponents. Think Ivy from Soul Calibur.]**

### Master of the Glaive
**[Benefits when wielding warglaives. Returning property, potential rebound off of targets, etc.]**

\columnbreak

### Mutation: X
**[A category of functional mutations, in comparison to the cosmetic mutations from Illidari Initiation. Each provides a specific benefit, along with an enhanced benefit while in Metamorphosis.]**

*(Grouped for sake of ease for now, will be separate invocations in the final version.)*

#### Mutation: Blood
**[Glowing blood effect. Acid blood? Improved hp?]**

#### Mutation: Claws
**[Can grow claws.]**

#### Mutation: Eyes
**[Can shoot lasers from your eyes. You transform into the metamorphosis form to use this ability in WoW anyway.]**

#### Mutation: Fangs
**[Grow fangs and bite attack. Lizardfolk style healing bite?]**

#### Mutation: Hooves
**[Increased speed? Stability?]**

#### Mutation: Horns
**[More sturdy horns than those in demonic mutations, allowing for gore effects.]**

#### Mutation: Scales
**[Provides bonus AC and fire resistance.]**

#### Mutation: Skin
**[Chameleon effect.]**

#### Mutation: Spikes
**[Causes damage to attackers.]**

#### Mutation: Tail
**[Tail becomes prehensile.]**

#### Mutation: Voice
**[Compelling voice. Shout attack when transformed?]**

#### Mutation: Wings
You gain the ability to manifest a pair of bat-like wings from your back. You can do so as a bonus action, or as a reaction made when falling, and they last until you dismiss them as a bonus action.

While your wings are manifested, your jump distance is doubled. You can also use the wings to glide, reducing your falling speed to 60 feet per round (taking no damage when landing) and allowing you to move horizontally up to 120 feet per round when doing so.

You can't manifest your wings while wearing armor unless the armor is made to accommodate them, and clothing not made to accommodate your wings might be destroyed when you manifest them.

While you are in Metamorphosis, you have a fly speed equal to twice your movement speed.

### Netherwalk
**[Can Dash, Disengage, and Dodge? Can't attack or be attacked, double speed, 1 round.]**

<div class='footnote'>PART 1 | CLASSES</div>

\pagebreakNum

### Shattered Souls 
When you reduce a hostile creature to 0 hit points, you gain temporary hit points equal to your Charisma modifier + your demon hunter level (minimum of 1). 

If the creature was a fiend or demon, you instead gain an amount equal to your Charisma modifier + twice your demon hunter level (minimum of 2).

### ???
*Prerequisite: Shattered Souls*

When you have temporary hit points gained from Shattered Souls, you have **[X benefit. Alternative: you regain 1 fel point when you do so.]**

### Torment
**[Deal psychic damage, force them to attack you.]**

**[Alternative/Additional option: can torture creatures for information.]**

