# Update 3.0-preview-2

<br />

These are the changes made to the class since the last update released for the class (3.0.0).

### General
- Finished the Quick Build section.
- Warglaives have been moved to the equipment document. They are now martial weapons instead of their own category.
- Instead of Intelligence being their secondary ability score, demon hunters now use Charisma. All Intelligence-based abilities have been adjusted.
- Illidari Initiation has been reworked. The ambush and warglaive-focused abilities have been removed, instead adding demonic detection and anti-possession effects, as well as cosmetic mutations. Fel points have been placed inside this ability, using the blood hunter's Hunter's Bane as a premise.
- Fel Points have been reworked, with the demon hunter having half as many but being able to risk self-damage by pushing beyond this limit. The Demon's Bite, Empower Wards, and Momentum abilities have been removed.
- Chaos Blades have been added, based on the blood hunter's Crimson Rite and the chaos bolt spell. 
- Spectral Sight has been reworded and several abilities have been added on: the ability to cast *detect magic*, bonuses on seeing through visual illusions, anti-demon perception powers, and an x-ray vision ability at 9th level.
- Invocations have been added.
- Metamorphosis has been reworked and moved to 11th level.
- Fighting Styles have been added at 2nd level.
- Subclass abilities are now at levels 3/6/10/15/18 instead of 3/6/10/17.
- Instinctive Hunter, A Hunter Above All Else, Demon Wings, Illidari Finesse, Cleansed By Flames, and Abyssal Resilience have been removed.
- An alternate version of Empowered Wards has been added at 13th level.
- Revealing Gaze now also gives a passive blindsight.
- Timeless Body has been moved to 17th level and expanded into Immortal Soul.
- Prepared allows for a choice between two secondary benefits.

### To Be Determined
- Should Immortal Soul have alternate benefits?
- All of the Mark of Havoc and Mark of Vengeance subclass features.
- The level 15 ability for the Mark of Wrath subclass.
- The details of most of the invocations.

\columnbreak

